---
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout.astro';

const title = "Terms of Service";
const description = "The rules of engagement for using this platform.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-12">
    <header class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-6">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-zinc-400">
        The rules of engagement. Simple, direct, and non-negotiable.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-zinc prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing or using this website, you agree to be bound by these terms. If you disagree with any part of the terms, you do not have permission to access the site. It's that simple.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Use License</h2>
      <p>
        The content on this site (articles, architecture diagrams, text) is provided for informational and educational purposes.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You may read, share, and link to the content.</li>
        <li>Code snippets provided in articles or devlogs are free to use in your own projects unless explicitly stated otherwise.</li>
        <li>You may not republish the content in its entirety on another platform and claim it as your own work. Attribution is required.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        The materials on this website are provided on an 'as is' basis. I make no warranties, expressed or implied, and hereby disclaim and negate all other warranties including, without limitation, implied warranties or conditions of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement of intellectual property or other violation of rights.
      </p>
      <p>
        Code breaks. APIs change. Use the techniques and code shared here at your own risk. I am not responsible if you deploy a snippet from a devlog and it brings down your production environment. Test your code.
      </p>

      <h2>4. User Conduct (Comments)</h2>
      <p>
        The comments section (powered by Giscus) is a place for technical discussion, feedback, and questions.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Keep it professional.</li>
        <li>No spam, no solicitation.</li>
        <li>Constructive criticism is welcome; toxicity is not.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        I reserve the right to moderate, edit, or delete any comments that violate these principles.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Links</h2>
      <p>
        This site may contain links to external websites that are not provided or maintained by or in any way affiliated with me. I do not guarantee the accuracy, relevance, timeliness, or completeness of any information on these external websites.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Modifications</h2>
      <p>
        I may revise these terms of service at any time without notice. By using this website you are agreeing to be bound by the then-current version of these terms of service.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500">
        Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
